The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 3: Trade union leaders today met finance minister Pranab Mukherjee and demanded the introduction of social security measures to help those who have lost their jobs. The labour leaders, in their pre-budget meeting, emphasised the need to take a fresh look at the labour issue in the backdrop of the economic slowdown.                             
	 Mumbai, June 3: Shipping firm Bharati Shipyard has priced its open offer for a 20 per cent stake in logistics firm Great Offshore at Rs 344 a share. The open offer would begin on July 25 and close on August 13.                             
	 Chicago, June 3: A US bankruptcy court has approved a raised bid from Emerisque Brands and S. Kumars Nationwide to acquire Hartmarx Corp, making way for the sale of the Chicago-based maker of President Barack Obamas suits.                            
	 Detroit/ New York, June 3: General Motors has reached a tentative deal to sell its Hummer brand to a Chinese company, Sichuan Tengzhong Heavy Industrial Machinery Co.                                                                                                                           
